  "stress_mechanisms_sources": {
    "_note": "Stress in Italian is not one phenomenon. Source tier drives confidence + who can assign it. Applied in order; later tiers confirm earlier.",
    "1_orthographic": "Final written accent IS the stress (città, perché, andò) -> tronca. Free, high.",
    "2_derivational_suffix": "Suffix fixes the class: -tà(final), -zione/-mente(piana), -issimo/-ico/-ibile(sdrucciola), dim. -ino/-etto/-one attract stress. Rule-assign, high.",
    "3_inflectional_paradigm": "Verb stress moves by tense/person given conjugation class: present 3pl is stem-stressed (pàrlano, telèfonano, àbitano => the sdrucciole/bisdrucciole source); remoto 3sg -ò (parlò, tronca); future/cond stress the ending. Derivable from a conjugation model -> powers the wordform layer. LEXICAL EXCEPTION: the -ere infinitive split (prèndere/scrìvere sdrucciole vs temére/dovére piane) is not predictable from spelling; mark per verb.",
    "4_pronunciation_lexicon": "Lexical residue (càmera, ìsola, tàvolo) + confirmation of 1-3. Sources: Wiktionary IPA, DOP, PhonItalia (~120k stress-marked), Morph-it!, espeak-ng.",
    "5_etymological_prior": "Learned/Greek words skew antepenult (mèdico, mùsica, tèlefono). Flag low-confidence only; never assert.",
    "syllabification_entanglement": "-ia hiatus (farmacìa) vs diphthong (stòria) is stress-dependent -> resolve stress FIRST, then syllabify."
  },
